# Aegis Hackathon Platform (AHP) вЂ” Implementation Plan

An **offline-first progressive web application** for managing hackathon events: schedules, rules, digital skills modules, multi-step project submissions вЂ” all fully functional without internet, with automatic background sync when connectivity returns.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | **Vite + React 18 + TypeScript** | Fast DX, tree-shaking, native PWA plugin |
| **Styling** | **Vanilla CSS** with custom properties design system | Full control, no framework overhead |
| **Routing** | **React Router v6** | Standard, SSR-ready if needed later |
| **Local DB** | **IndexedDB** via `idb` wrapper | Structured offline storage with promises |
| **PWA** | **vite-plugin-pwa** (Workbox) | Precaching, runtime caching, background sync |
| **Backend** | **Express + TypeScript + SQLite** (via `better-sqlite3`) | Zero-config DB, single-binary deploy |
| **Auth** | **JWT** (access + refresh tokens) | Stateless, works offline once issued |
| **File Storage** | Local `uploads/` directory | Simple, can swap to S3 later |

---

