## Proposed Changes

### Phase 0 вЂ” Scaffolding & Foundation

#### [NEW] Root project setup
- Initialize npm workspace with `client/` and `server/` packages
- Configure shared TypeScript settings
- Add `.gitignore`, `README.md`

#### [NEW] `client/` вЂ” Vite React PWA app
- Scaffold with `create-vite` (React + TypeScript template)
- Install dependencies: `react-router-dom`, `idb`, `vite-plugin-pwa`
- Configure `vite.config.ts` with PWA plugin (precache app shell, schedules, rules data)
- Set up `manifest.json` (name, icons, theme color, display: standalone)

#### [NEW] `server/` вЂ” Express API
- Initialize with TypeScript, `better-sqlite3`, `multer`, `jsonwebtoken`, `bcryptjs`
- Create SQLite schema: `users`, `submissions`, `skill_progress`, `sync_queue`
- Wire up basic health-check route

---

### Phase 1 вЂ” Frontend & UI

#### Design System (`client/src/styles/`)
- `tokens.css`: CSS custom properties for colors (dark/light), typography scale, spacing, radii, shadows
- `reset.css`: Modern CSS reset
- `global.css`: Base element styles

#### Layout Components (`client/src/components/layout/`)
- `AppShell.tsx`: Responsive layout with mobile bottom nav + desktop sidebar
- `Navbar.tsx`: Logo, nav links, network status indicator, user menu
- `Sidebar.tsx`: Desktop navigation panel

#### Pages (`client/src/pages/`)
- `Home.tsx`: Dashboard landing with event countdown, quick links
- `Schedule.tsx`: Timeline/agenda view of hackathon events, filterable by day
- `Rules.tsx`: Formatted rules document with accordion sections
- `SkillModules.tsx`: Card grid of digital skill lessons with progress bars
- `SubmitProject.tsx`: Multi-step form wizard:
  - Step 1: Team info (name, members)
  - Step 2: Project details (title, description, category)
  - Step 3: Media upload (images, video, documents)
  - Step 4: Review & submit
- `Login.tsx`: Auth form (login / register toggle)

---

### Phase 2 вЂ” Offline Capabilities

#### Service Worker (`client/src/sw.ts` via `vite-plugin-pwa`)
- **Precache**: App shell HTML, CSS, JS bundles, fonts, icons
- **Runtime cache**: Schedule JSON (StaleWhileRevalidate), Rules content (CacheFirst), API responses (NetworkFirst)
- **Offline fallback**: Serve cached page when offline

#### IndexedDB Layer (`client/src/lib/db.ts`)
- Database: `ahp-db`, version 1
- Object stores:
  - `submissions` вЂ” queued project submissions (status: draft | queued | synced)
  - `skillProgress` вЂ” module completion states per user
  - `syncQueue` вЂ” generic sync action queue with timestamps
  - `mediaFiles` вЂ” blob storage for uploaded files pending sync
- Helper functions: `addSubmission()`, `getSubmissions()`, `updateSyncStatus()`, etc.

#### Offline Flow
- All form data saves to IndexedDB immediately
- Network status context provides `isOnline` flag across the app
- Visual indicators: "Saved offline" badge, pending sync count

---

### Phase 3 вЂ” Synchronization Engine

#### Background Sync (`client/src/lib/sync.ts`)
- Register `sync` event tag `ahp-sync` in service worker
- On `sync` event: read all `queued` items from IndexedDB, POST to server
- On success: mark items as `synced` in IndexedDB
- On failure: leave as `queued` for retry

#### Conflict Resolution
- Each record carries `updatedAt` (ISO timestamp) and `version` (incrementing integer)
- Server compares incoming `version` against stored `version`
- If incoming в‰Ґ stored в†’ accept. If incoming < stored в†’ reject with 409 + server copy
- Client resolves by re-fetching latest and notifying user of conflict

#### Media Upload
- Large files chunked into в‰¤ 5 MB parts
- Upload endpoint accepts multipart chunks with `X-Chunk-Index` / `X-Total-Chunks` headers
- Server reassembles on final chunk receipt

---

### Phase 4 вЂ” Backend API

#### Auth Routes (`server/src/routes/auth.ts`)
| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Create user account |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Issue JWT tokens |
| POST | `/api/auth/refresh` | Refresh access token |

#### Sync Routes (`server/src/routes/sync.ts`)
| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/sync` | Bulk receive queued data |
| POST | `/api/sync/media` | Chunked media upload |
| GET | `/api/sync/status` | Check sync status for user |

#### Submission Routes (`server/src/routes/submissions.ts`)
| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/submissions` | List user submissions |
| GET | `/api/submissions/:id` | Submission detail |

#### Admin Routes (`server/src/routes/admin.ts`)
| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/admin/submissions` | All submissions (filterable) |
| GET | `/api/admin/users` | User list with progress |
| GET | `/api/admin/stats` | Dashboard stats |

#### Database Schema (`server/src/db/schema.sql`)
- `users`: id, name, email, password_hash, role, created_at
- `submissions`: id, user_id, team_name, project_title, description, category, status, version, created_at, updated_at
- `submission_media`: id, submission_id, file_path, file_type, chunk_status
- `skill_progress`: id, user_id, module_id, status, completed_at, version
- `sync_log`: id, user_id, action, entity_type, entity_id, timestamp, status

---

### Phase 5 вЂ” Admin Dashboard

#### Admin Pages (`client/src/pages/admin/`)
- `Dashboard.tsx`: Stats cards (total submissions, active users, sync success rate), recent activity feed
- `Submissions.tsx`: Data table with search, filter by status/category/date, sort, pagination
- `SubmissionDetail.tsx`: Full submission with media preview, timeline of sync events
- `Progress.tsx`: User progress heatmap/table across skill modules

